[[File:Guardiandroid.png|thumb|C-3PO wearing the shell of an HK Guardian Droid.]]
{{Quote|Oh, goodness&hellip;the empty shell of a ''Guardian Droid''! I haven't seen one of them in ''ages''! It's a pity they're no longer in service&hellip;their armor was quite impervious to laser fire!''"<br />"''Bwoop bweep!''"<br />"''Yes, Artoo&hellip;and when they realized nothing could ''harm'' them&hellip;they ''were'' a bit difficult to control!|C-3PO and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] discuss the HK Guardian Droid|<ref name="The Ultimate Weapon">[[Droids (1986) 2|''Droids'' (1986) 2]]</ref>}}
The ''' HK Guardian Droid''' was a model of [[Droid/Legends|droid]] whose superior [[Armor/Legends|armor]] was almost impervious to [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] fire.<ref name="The Droids Re-Animated, Part 1">{{SW|url=news/the-droids-re-animated-part-1|series=The Droids Re-Animated|text=Part 1|nolive=1}}</ref> After realizing this, they became difficult to control<ref name="The Ultimate Weapon" /> and ultimately contributed to the common prejudice against droids.<ref name="The Droids Re-Animated, Part 1" /> HKs were no longer in service by the early [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].<ref name="The Ultimate Weapon" />

When [[Lonn Idd]]'s [[Lonn Idd's repair station|repair station]] was under attack by the [[Fromm Gang/Legends|Fromm Gang]], the [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] donned the aged shell of an HK Guardian Droid stored in a spare parts storage room, allowing [[Gender/Legends|him]] to survive a group of [[hover guard]]s' [[light stunning blaster]]s and destroy the [[Sentry droid/Legends|sentry droids]].<ref name="The Ultimate Weapon" />

